).

Insertions associated with the disruption of secretory regulation mapped to two distinct areas of PcrV (
). One set (EZ119, EZ120, EZ131, EZ134, EZ138, and EZ279) mapped to the end of the globular domain and to the central coiled-coil domain (
). The second set (EZ44, EZ52, and EZ64) mapped to the predicted N-terminal globular domain. Interestingly, the derivatives with the constitutive-secretion phenotype segregated into noncytotoxic and cytotoxic groups. Insertions adjacent to or within the coiled-coil region (1
group) prevented both translocation and regulated secretion of ExoU (gray boxes in
